<!doctype html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <title>CSS and the Cascade</title>
  <style>
    p {
      color:blue;
      font-family: Times;
      font-size: 8px;
}
    .red{
      color:red;
      font-size: 16px;
}
    #special{
      font-family: Arial;
      font-size: 24px;
}
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <p>Paragraph</p>
  <p class ="green">Paragraph</p>
  <p class ="red">Paragraph</p>
  <p class ="red" id ="special">Paragraph</p>

  <h3>Cascading</h3>
  <h4>Styles cascade down until they run into a new rule that is more specific.</h4>
  <h5>Why do each p tag display the way it does?</h5>




</body>
</html>
